extends ./layout/default.jade

block variable
    - var chapter_num = "5.4"
    - var chapter_title_en = "Life and Death"
    - var chapter_title_cn = "生死攸關"


block title
    title MGS #{chapter_num} - #{chapter_title_en} (#{chapter_title_cn})

block container
    h2.title.title-en
        span.title-num #{chapter_num}
        strong.title-en
            | #{chapter_title_en}
        strong.title-cn
            | #{chapter_title_cn}

    .section
        .dialog
            em.name.name-meryl
                | Meryl
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | That's the second time I've been able to sneak up on the legendary Solid Snake. (Meryl has her rifle pressed against Snake's back, unmenacingly.  Snake turns around to look at her.)
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | You're Meryl?  There's no way you could pass for a man for long.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-meryl
                | Meryl
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | What do you mean?  Hey!  Men aren't allowed in here.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | I had no idea you were so feminine.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-meryl
                | Meryl
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | This is no time to try and hit on me, Snake.  Besides, it's a waste of time.  When I joined up they gave me psychotherapy to destroy my interest in men.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Same smart mouth.  You're Meryl all right.  Are you hurt?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-meryl
                | Meryl
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Not yet.  After all, I was disguised as a Genome Soldier.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | So why'd you change?  You'd be better off dressed like one of them.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-meryl
                | Meryl
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | I got tired of disguising myself.  The truth is... the uniform smelled like blood. (Snake sees Meryl's tattoo on her left arm.)
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | What's that mark?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-meryl
                | Meryl
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Huh?  Oh, this?  It's a paint tattoo.  It's not real.  I was a fan of FOX-HOUND way back.  When guys like you and my uncle were in it.  None of that gene therapy like there is today.  You guys were real heroes.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | There are no heroes in war.  All the heroes I know are either dead... or in prison.  One or the other.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-meryl
                | Meryl
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | But Snake.  You're a hero.  Aren't you?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | I'm just a man who's good at what he does.  Killing.  There's no winning or losing for a mercenary.  The only winners in war are the people.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-meryl
                | Meryl
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | That's right.  And you fight for the people.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | I've never fought for anyone but myself. I've got no purpose in life.  No ultimate goal.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-meryl
                | Meryl
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Come on.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | It's only when I'm cheating death on the battlefield.  The only time I feel truly alive.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-meryl
                | Meryl
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Seeing other people die makes you feel alive, huh?  You love war and don't want it to stop... Is it the same with all great soldiers throughout history?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Why didn't you contact me?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-meryl
                | Meryl
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | My Codec was broken.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Is that all?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-meryl
                | Meryl
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Shouldn't you just be happy that we met up like this!?  How did you recognize me in disguise?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | I never forget a lady.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-meryl
                | Meryl
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | So there's something you like about me, huh?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Yeah, you've got a great butt.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-meryl
                | Meryl
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Oh, I see.  First it's my eyes, now it's my butt.  What's next?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | On the battlefield you never think about what's next.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-meryl
                | Meryl
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | So Snake... how are the negotiations doing?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | No progress.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-meryl
                | Meryl
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | So, it's all up to you, huh?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Somebody's got to prevent them from launching a nuclear missile.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-meryl
                | Meryl
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | There are two ways.  Either we destroy Metal Gear, or...
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | ...we override the detonation code.  You got the card keys from Baker?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-meryl
                | Meryl
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Card keys? (Meryl reaches into her shirt and pulls out a card key.)
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-meryl
                | Meryl
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | You mean this?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Where are the others?  There should be three keys.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-meryl
                | Meryl
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | This is all I've got.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Where could the other two be?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-meryl
                | Meryl
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | I have no idea, but they must be somewhere.  If we can't find them we'll have no choice but to destroy Metal Gear.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Metal Gear is in an underground maintenance base to the north.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-meryl
                | Meryl
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Take me too.  I know this place better than you do.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | You'll just slow me down.  You don't have enough battle experience.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-meryl
                | Meryl
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | I won't slow you down.  I promise.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | And what if you do?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-meryl
                | Meryl
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Then you can shoot me.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | I don't like to waste bullets.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-meryl
                | Meryl
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Got it.  I'll be careful.  Y'know... I don't use makeup the way other women do... I hardly ever look at myself in the mirror. I've always despised that kind of woman.  I always dreamed of becoming a soldier.  But I was wrong.  It wasn't really my dream.  My father... he was killed in action when I was younger.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | You wanted to follow in your father's footsteps?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-meryl
                | Meryl
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Not really.  I thought that if I became a soldier I could understand him better.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | So are you a soldier yet?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-meryl
                | Meryl
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | I thought I was until today.  But... now I understand.  The truth is I was just afraid of looking at myself.  Afraid of having to make my own decisions in life.  But I'm not going to lie to myself any more.  It's time I took a long, hard look at myself... I want to know who I am, what I'm capable of.  I want to know why I've lived the way I've lived until now.  I want to know. (Snake reaches for his SOCOM and loads a clip into it.)
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Take a good look.  You won't get anothert chance for a while. You should wash your face while you're at it.  This isn't a training exercise.  Our lives are riding on this.  There are no heroes or heroins.  If you lose, you're worm food.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-meryl
                | Meryl
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Yeah. (Snake spots Meryl's FAMAS on the ground.)
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Is that FAMAS functional?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-meryl
                | Meryl
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Unfortunately it's out of ammo.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Where'd ya' get that Desert Eagle?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-meryl
                | Meryl
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | I found it in the armory.  It's a .50 caliber Action Express. There was a SOCOM pistol too, but I chose this.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Hmmm.  So I got a leftover, huh.  Isn't that gun a little big for a girl.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-meryl
                | Meryl
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Don't worry, I can handle it. (Snake holds his SOCOM out to Meryl.)
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | C'mon.  Use my .45.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-meryl
                | Meryl
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Listen, I've used a gun like this since I was 8 years old.  I'm more comforatble with it than I am with a bra. (Meryl pulls a clip of ammo out of her shirt and reloads her pistol.)
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-meryl
                | Meryl
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | If we're going to go to the north, we'll have to go through the Commander's Room on this floor.  The overland route is blocked by glaciers.  The door to the commander's room is security level five.  This card will open it. (Meryl pulls out a card.)
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-meryl
                | Meryl
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | It was inside the pocket of the uniform I was wearing. (She hands the card to Snake.)
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Looks like he must have been guarding someplace important.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-meryl
                | Meryl
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Okay, let's go.  I know this place better than you.  I'll be point man.  Follow me. (Meryl exits the bathroom, Snake follows her.)
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-meryl
                | Meryl
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | That's strange.  There's no guard.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | What happened to the music?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-meryl
                | Meryl
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | I'll keep a look out.  Make sure you're ready, okay? (Snake and Meryl reach the entrance to the commander's room.)
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-meryl
                | Meryl
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | My head! ...Ooh.  It hurts! (Meryl kneels on the floor clutching her head.)
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | What's wrong?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-meryl
                | Meryl
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Don't come here, Snake! (We see views of the commanders room, as if somebody is waiting for them.)
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Are you okay?  What happened? (Meryl stands up.  When she speaks her voice sounds different.)
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-meryl
                | Meryl
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | I'm fine.  Let's go. (Meryl walks to the door of the Commander's Room.)
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-meryl
                | Meryl
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | C'mon Mr. FOX-HOUND.  The commander is waiting. (They go into the Commander's Room.) (Meryl begins to jerk around.)
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-meryl
                | Meryl
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Ah! (She points her handgun at Snake.  She begins to walk towards him, slowly. When she speaks her voice sounds strange.)
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-meryl
                | Meryl
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Snake... do you... like me?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | What the!?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-meryl
                | Meryl
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Do you like me?  Hold me, Snake.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | What's wrong?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-meryl
                | Meryl
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Hurry... hurry!  Make love to me!!  Snake, I want you!! (We now see Psycho Mantis behind Meryl.  He is controlling her.)
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Who's that!?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-mantis
                | Mantis
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Huh?  You don't like girls? (Campbell calls on the Codec.)
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-campbell
                | Campbell
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Snake, Meryl's not herself.  Don't use your weapon.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-naomi
                | Naomi
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | It's psycho Mantis.  He's controlling Meryl.  That tune is his mind control music.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-campbell
                | Campbell
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Don't use your weapon.  Try to knock her out. (Snake knocks her out easily.)
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-mantis
                | Mantis
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Useless woman! (Snake takes not of Mantis' optical camouflage.)
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Optic camouflage, huh?  I hope that's not your only trick.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-mantis
                | Mantis
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | You!  You doubt my power!? (Snake ignores Mantis and checks on Meryl, to make sure she isn't hurt.)
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-mantis
                | Mantis
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Now, I will show you why I am the most powerful practitioner of psychokinesis and telepathy in the world. (Mantis takes off his camouflage and we can see that he is floating in the air without any outside supports.  Snake is a bit surprised by this, he steps backwards.)
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-mantis
                | Mantis
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | No... there's no need for words, Snake.  I am Psycho Mantis. That's right... this is no trick.  It is true power. (Snake whips out his SOCOM and points it at Mantis.)
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-mantis
                | Mantis
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | It's useless.  I told you... I can read your every thought. Now... let me read your mind.  No... perhaps I should say your past. (At this point there are several things Mantis can say.  He will put together a combination of these to tell Snake somthing.)
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-mantis
                | Mantis
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Still don't believe me?  Now I'll read more deeply into your soul.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        p
            | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------ * You're a careless man, aren't you? ------------------------------------------------------------------------------ * And you're a poor warrior as well. ------------------------------------------------------------------------------ * And the same goes with traps. ------------------------------------------------------------------------------ * However you are skillful at eluding traps. ------------------------------------------------------------------------------ * However you are a skilled warrior. ------------------------------------------------------------------------------ * You like brute force... ------------------------------------------------------------------------------ * But you are careless around traps. ------------------------------------------------------------------------------ * You are extremely cautious around traps. ------------------------------------------------------------------------------ * You are a very methodical man. ------------------------------------------------------------------------------ * The type that always kicks his tires before he leaves. ------------------------------------------------------------------------------ * And yet you are rather ineffective in battle. ------------------------------------------------------------------------------ * And you need to beware of traps as well. ------------------------------------------------------------------------------ * It seems that you are careful with traps. ------------------------------------------------------------------------------ * You are a highly skilled warrior, ------------------------------------------------------------------------------ * well suited to this stealth mission. ------------------------------------------------------------------------------ * However, traps are your weak point. ------------------------------------------------------------------------------ * You are extremely careful of traps. ------------------------------------------------------------------------------ * You are either very cautious, ------------------------------------------------------------------------------ * or you are a coward... ------------------------------------------------------------------------------ * Still don't believe me? ------------------------------------------------------------------------------ * Now I'll read more deeply into your soul. ------------------------------------------------------------------------------ * Ah...I can see into your mind... ------------------------------------------------------------------------------ * So you like SUIKODEN? ------------------------------------------------------------------------------ * So you like AZURE DREAMS? ------------------------------------------------------------------------------ * You like fighting games, don't you? ------------------------------------------------------------------------------ * So you like adventure games? ------------------------------------------------------------------------------ * You enjoy role-playing games. ------------------------------------------------------------------------------ * You like action games! ------------------------------------------------------------------------------ * You like to play sports games! ------------------------------------------------------------------------------ * You like arcade games. ------------------------------------------------------------------------------ * I see that you enjoy Konami games. ------------------------------------------------------------------------------ * So you like VANDAL HEARTS. ------------------------------------------------------------------------------ * I can read you like an open book! ------------------------------------------------------------------------------ * Hmmm. You have saved often. ------------------------------------------------------------------------------ * You are a prudent person. ------------------------------------------------------------------------------ * Hmmm. You have not saved often. ------------------------------------------------------------------------------ * You are somewhat reckless. ------------------------------------------------------------------------------ * Hmmm...Your memory is completely clean. ------------------------------------------------------------------------------ * And you are neglecting to save this game as well. ------------------------------------------------------------------------------ * You will regret it. ------------------------------------------------------------------------------ (Mantis tries something else.)
        .dialog
            em.name.name-mantis
                | Mantis
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | You still don't believe me?  I will show you my psychokinetic power.  Put your controller on the floor.  Put it down as flat as you can... that's good.  Now I will move your controller by the power of my will alone!! (Mantis now moves the controller by activating the vibration function.)
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-mantis
                | Mantis
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | What do you think now!?  Can you feel my power now!?  The demonstration is over!! (Snake battles Mantis.  Mantis begins to control Meryl again.)
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-mantis
                | Mantis
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | You are powerful indeed, but I know your weak point!
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Meryl.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-mantis
                | Mantis
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Stand right where he can see you... and blow your brains out!!!
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-meryl
                | Meryl
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Aaah!!
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Stop! Meryl!! (Snake must once again knock Meryl out.  Mantis is immensly frustrated when he succedes.)
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-mantis
                | Mantis
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Why!?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-mantis
                | Mantis
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Yes, stand right there and blow your brains out. (After Mantis is defeated, Snake calls Campbell on the Codec.)
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Colonel, your niece is going to be okay.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-campbell
                | Campbell
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Thanks, Snake. I owe you one.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Now that Mantis is beaten, Meryl's brainwashing is going to wear off, right Naomi?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-naomi
                | Naomi
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Yes.  Why did you go so far out of your way to save her?  For Campbell's sake... or... maybe it's because you like her?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | I don't want to see any woman die right in front of me.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-naomi
                | Naomi
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Oh really?  Since when did anybody's death bother you so much?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-campbell
                | Campbell
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Naomi!  It's true that Snake has killed a lot of people, that doesn't mean he doesn't have a heart.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | It's okay, Colonel... she's right.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-naomi
                | Naomi
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | ....... (Snake walks over to Mantis.)
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-mantis
                | Mantis
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | So... you used the other... I... I wasn't able to read the future...
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | A strong man doesn't need to read the future.  He makes his own.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-mantis
                | Mantis
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Perhaps so... But I will also read your future... (Meryl gets up from the floor.)
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-mantis
                | Mantis
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | To get to Metal Gear's underground maintenance base... you have to go through that hidden door.  There's a hidden door behind the bookcase.  The overland route... it's blocked by frozen glaciers. Go past the communications towers.  Then use the tower's walkway. (While Mantis is talking we see what he is talking about.  Snake kneels down beside Mantis.)
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Why are you telling me this?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-mantis
                | Mantis
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | I can read people's minds.  In my lifetime I have read the pasts, presents, and futures of thousands upon thousands of men and women. (Snake takes off Mantis's mask.  Meryl grabs her mouth, apparently horrified.)
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-meryl
                | Meryl
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Oh... gross...
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-mantis
                | Mantis
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | And each mind that I peered into was stuffed with the same single object of obsession.  That selfish and atavistic dsire to pass on one's seed... it was enough to make me sick.  Every living thing on this planet exists to mindlessly pass on their DNA.  We're designed that way.  And that's why there is war.  But you... you are different... You're the same as us.  We have no past, no future.  We live in the moment.  That's out only purpose.  Humans weren't designed to bring eachother happiness.  From the moment we're thrown into this world, we're fated to bring each other nothing but pain and misery.  The first person who's mind I dove into was my father's.  I saw nothing but disgust and hatred for me in his heart.  My mother died in childbirth... and he despised me for it... I thought my father was going to kill me. (Now we see Mantis's spirit or soul floating above him.)
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-mantis
                | Mantis
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | That's when my future dissapeared.  I lost my past as well.  When I came to, the village was engulfed in flames...
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Are you saying you burned your village down to bury your past?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-mantis
                | Mantis
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | I see that you have suffered the same trauma. (Mantis laughs feebly.)
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-mantis
                | Mantis
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | We are truly the same, you and I... The world is a more interesting place with people like you in it... I never agreed with the Boss's revolution.  His dreams of world conquest do not interest me.  I just wanted an excuse to kill as many people as I could. (Meryl is taken aback by this.)
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-meryl
                | Meryl
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | You monster!
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Let him talk.  He doesn't have much time left.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-mantis
                | Mantis
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | I've seen true evil.  You Snake.  You're just like the Boss... No, you're worse.  Compared to you, I'm not so bad. (Mantis nods to Meryl.)
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-mantis
                | Mantis
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | I read her mind as well.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Meryl's?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-mantis
                | Mantis
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | I saw you there... you have a large place in heart. (Meryl touches Snake's shoulder.)
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | A large place?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-mantis
                | Mantis
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Yes. A large place.  But I do not know if your futures lie together.  I have a last request.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | What is it?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-mantis
                | Mantis
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | My mask... put it back on.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Okay. (Snake hesitates to put it back on while Mantis is talking.  He holds it over his face.)
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-mantis
                | Mantis
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Like this... other people's thoughts force their way into my mind. Before I die... I want to be by myself.  I want to be left alone in my own world. (Snake places the mask on Mantis' face and secures it with the straps.)
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-mantis
                | Mantis
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | I'll open the door for you. (Mantis reaches out a hand and moves it so that the bookshelf blocking the door moves out of the way.)
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-mantis
                | Mantis
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | If you want to find your future, go through that door.  This is the first time I've ever used my power to help someone.  It's strange... it feels... kind of... nice. (Mantis' head lolls to one side.  Snake pauses for a moment and then stands up.)
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Let's go, Meryl.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-meryl
                | Meryl
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | I'm sorry...
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Meryl?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-meryl
                | Meryl
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | How could I let Mantis control my mind like that...
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | If you're going to doubt yourself, I'll leave you here.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-meryl
                | Meryl
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | You're right.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Never doubt yourself.  Just let it make you stronger.  Learn something from it.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-meryl
                | Meryl
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | You're right.  I'm sorry.  I won't do it again. (Snake turns to leave.)
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-meryl
                | Meryl
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Snake, can I ask you something?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | What!?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-meryl
                | Meryl
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | About what Mantis said... I was just wondering...
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | What?  What's the problem now?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-meryl
                | Meryl
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Oh no... nothing.  So tell me, Snake.  What's your name?  Your real name?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Name means nothing on the battlfield.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-meryl
                | Meryl
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | How old are you?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | OLd enough to know what death looks like.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-meryl
                | Meryl
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Any family?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | No, but I was raised by many people.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-meryl
                | Meryl
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Is there anyone you like?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | I've never been interested in anyone else's life...
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-meryl
                | Meryl
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | So you are all alone.  Just like Mantis said.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Other people just complicate my life.  I don't like to get involved.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-meryl
                | Meryl
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | You're a sad, lonely man.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | C'mon... let's go. (Snake and Meryl head out the hidden door.)
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-meryl
                | Meryl
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Okay, I'll take point again.  Follow me. (Snake has to follow Meryl through a cave with a dozen or so wolf-dogs patrolling it.  When they see him they attack him.  Eventually, Snake meets up with Meryl on the other end of the cave.)
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-meryl
                | Meryl
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | What's wrong, Snake? I thought you were good with dogs? (They go into the next room.  They find themselves in the Underground Passage. Meryl stops Snake from advancing, because of mines.)
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-meryl
                | Meryl
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Hold up, Snake!  This place is mined.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | The radar isn't working.  And since we can't use the mine detector either...
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-meryl
                | Meryl
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Leave it to me... (Meryl walks through the mine field and gets to the other side unscathed.)
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | How did you know where the mines were?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-meryl
                | Meryl
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | When Mantis dove into my mind, I could see where the mines were placed. Are you impressed?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Well... a little bit. (Now we see a set of crosshairs centered on Snake.  They move to Meryl.  She turns around.)
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Meryl!!
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-meryl
                | Meryl
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | What is it? (The laser point on Meryl moves down to her right thigh.)
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Meryl, get down!!! (Meryl is shot in the leg.)
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-meryl
                | Meryl
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Aaaaaahhhh!!
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Meryl!! (Snake quickly takes cover behind the wall and looks over to Meryl.  She is on her knees now.  She is shot again, this time in her left leg.)
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-meryl
                | Meryl
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Aaaaaaaaahhhh!!! (She collapses in a pool of blood and tries to reach her gun beside her.  The sniper acts quickly and shoots her in the arm.)
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-meryl
                | Meryl
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Aaaaaaaghhhh!!! (Meryl gives up and lies on her back, bleeding badly.  Snake tries to move towards her, but he is met by a bullet that hist the wall right near him.)
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-meryl
                | Meryl
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Snake.... leave me and run...
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Meryl...
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-meryl
                | Meryl
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | I guess... I am a rookie after all...
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Don't worry, Meryl.  It's me they want.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-meryl
                | Meryl
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Even I know that, it's the oldest trick in the book.  The sniper's using me for bait to lure you out.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Damn!!
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-meryl
                | Meryl
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Shoot me, Snake!!
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | No!
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-meryl
                | Meryl
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | My gun... I can't reach it by myself.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Don't move!
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-meryl
                | Meryl
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | I promised... I wouldn't slow you down!  I... I... I can still help... I want to help you!
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Quiet down!  Save your strength!
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-meryl
                | Meryl
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | I was a fool, I wanted to be a soldier.  But war is ugly... There's nothing glamorous about it.  Snake, please!  Save yourself.  Go on living and don't give up on people!  Don't forget me... Now get out of here! (Snake's Codec is ringing.)
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-campbell
                | Campbell
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Meryl!  Damn!! Snake, it's a trap!  Sniper's trick to lure you out. The sniper's waiting for you to go and help Meryl so he can pick you off... Don't do it!
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-naomi
                | Naomi
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | It must be Sniper Wolf, FOX-HOUND's best shooter.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Sniper's usually work in pairs, but this one's alone, huh?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-naomi
                | Naomi
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | I know her.  She can wait for hours, days, or weeks, it doesn't matter to her.  She's just watching and waiting for you to expose yourself.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Maybe so, but Meryl can't hold out that long...
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-naomi
                | Naomi
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Snake, can you see Wolf from where you are?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | There's no where to hide between here and the tower... she must be on the second floor of the tower.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-campbell
                | Campbell
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | If Wolf is in the Communications Tower, she can see you perfectly! It's the classic sniper's position!!  At that distance you won't be able to hit her with a standard weapon either!  You'll need a sniper rifle.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Colonel!  Take it easy.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-campbell
                | Campbell
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | ......
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | I'm going to save Meryl no matter what it takes.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-campbell
                | Campbell
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Okay, thanks.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-naomi
                | Naomi
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | ......
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | What's wrong, Naomi?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-naomi
                | Naomi
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Nothing... I'm just surprised you're willing to sacrifice yourself... you've got the genes of a soldier, not a savior.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Trying to say that I'm only interested in saving my own skin?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-naomi
                | Naomi
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | I wouldn't go that far but...
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | I don't know what the hell my genes look like and I don't care. I operate on instinct.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-naomi
                | Naomi
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Like an animal?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | I'm going to save Meryl.  I don't need an excuse.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-naomi
                | Naomi
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Okay...
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | And I'm not doing it for someone else either.  I'm going to save Meryl by myself.  Colonel, don't worry!
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-campbell
                | Campbell
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Snake, thanks.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-naomi
                | Naomi
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | I understand.  I'm sorry. (Snake goes off to find the PSG1.  He finds it in Armory.)
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-campbell
                | Campbell
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | You've got a PSG1?  Hurry up and save Meryl! (Snake hurries off to the Underground Passage.  He battles Wolf and defeats her.  Meryl has been taken away so he proceeds through the Underground Passage looking for her.  He reaches the door on the other end but three heavily armed guards rappel from the ceiling behind him.)
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-guards
                | Guards
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Freeze!! (Snake holds up his hands and looks at the guards, waiting for something to happen.)
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-wolf
                | Wolf
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | It's hard to miss when you're this close. (Snake sees Wolf approaching him with her rifle pointed squarely at his chest.)
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-wolf
                | Wolf
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Toss your weapon over here.  Slowly... (Snake slides his SOCOM across the floor, one of the guards picks it up. Wolf and one of the guards go closer to him.)
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-wolf
                | Wolf
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | You are a fool to come down here.. stupid man!
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | A lady sniper, huh?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-wolf
                | Wolf
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Didn't you know that two thirds of the world's greatest assassins are women?  Do you want to die now?  Or after your female friend? Which will it be?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | I'll die after I kill you. (She lets out a small laugh.)
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-wolf
                | Wolf
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Is that right?  Well at least you've got spirit. (Wolf lets down her gun and runs her hand through her hair.)
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-wolf
                | Wolf
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | I am Sniper Wolf and I always kill what I aim at. (She walks over to him and reaches up to his face.)
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-wolf
                | Wolf
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | You're my... special prey.  Got it? (She scratches Snake's cheek, drawing blood. Snake lets out a small grunt.)
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-wolf
                | Wolf
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | I've left my mark on you... I won't forget it.  Until I kill you, you're all I'll think about. (The guard closest to Snake whacks him in the head with the but of his rifle. Snake falls to the floor, unconscious.)
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Uuuuhh!!
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-guard
                | Guard
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Take him away! (Snake is dragged away back down the Underground Passage, away from where he was heading. We now see a faint outline of something onscreen, there are distant voices.)
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-liquid
                | Liquid
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Don't kill him yet. I want him alive.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-ocelot
                | Ocelot
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Leave it to me.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-liquid
                | Liquid
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | I want no more accidents like that DARPA Chief.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-wolf
                | Wolf
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Yes.  He's my target.  Mine alone. (We now see an overhead medical lamp.  There are background noises of computers running.)
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-liquid
                | Liquid
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Can you hear me, Solid Snake?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-wolf
                | Wolf
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | He's tougher than I thought...
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-liquid
                | Liquid
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Do you know who I am?  I always knew that one day I would meet you. The man who stole what was rightly mine... the man who stole my birthright.  Me? I'm the man you stole everything good from. And now, after the sacrifice of our brothers... after 30 long years, finally the two of us meet.  The brother of light and the brother of dark.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-wolf
                | Wolf
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Do you need his DNA too?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-liquid
                | Liquid
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Yes, I want a sample while he's still alive.  We need it to correct the Genome Soldier's mutations.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-wolf
                | Wolf
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Then we'll be able to cure them?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-liquid
                | Liquid
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | No.  We still have to get our hands on Big Boss's DNA.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-wolf
                | Wolf
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Have they given in to our demands yet?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-liquid
                | Liquid
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Not yet.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-wolf
                | Wolf
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | They won't give in.  They're all hypocrites, every one of them.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-liquid
                | Liquid
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Is that your opinion as a Kurd?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-wolf
                | Wolf
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | They always put politics first.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-liquid
                | Liquid
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | That's right.  That's why they want to avoid any leak about their precious new nuclear weapon.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-ocelot
                | Ocelot
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Boss, it looks like our friend is awake. (Snake is abruptly brought down somewhere to face Liquid, who is standing in front of him.  Snake is strapped into a revolving metal bed.)
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-liquid
                | Liquid
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | There definitely is a resemblance.  Don't you think, little brother? Or should I say big brother?  I'm not sure... Anyway, it doesn't matter.  You and I are both the last surviving "sons of Big Boss". (Liquid's cell phone rings, he pulls it out hurridly.)
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-liquid
                | Liquid
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | It's me... Really?  Then what?  Those idiots!  All right Raven. I'll be right there. (Liquid puts it away and talks to Wolf and Ocelot.)
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-liquid
                | Liquid
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | They're not responding to our demands.  We'll launch the first one in 10 hours as planned.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-wolf
                | Wolf
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Damn Americans!!
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-ocelot
                | Ocelot
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Looks like you read them wrong.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-liquid
                | Liquid
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Something's funny... Normally the Americans are the first ones to the negotiating table.  They must think they've go something up their sleeves.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-ocelot
                | Ocelot
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | So it's come down to it, has it.  We're going to launch that nuke and ride it all the way into history.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-liquid
                | Liquid
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | I've got to take care of some launch preparations.  You're in charge here, Ocelot. (Ocelot speaks to Sniper Wolf.)
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-ocelot
                | Ocelot
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | What about you?  Wanna stay for the show?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-wolf
                | Wolf
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | I'm not interested.  It's time to feed the family. (Wolf shakes around a small canister of pills.  She takes a few out and swallows them.)
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-ocelot
                | Ocelot
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | So, you prefer your wolves to my show, huh?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-liquid
                | Liquid
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Ocelot, don't screw up like you did with the Chief.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-ocelot
                | Ocelot
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Yes, I know.  That was an accident.  I didn't think a pencil pusher like him would be so tough.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-liquid
                | Liquid
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Well... his mental defenses were reinforced by hypnotherapy.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-ocelot
                | Ocelot
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Boss, what about that ninja?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-liquid
                | Liquid
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | He killed 12 men.  Whoever he is, he's some kind of lunatic.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-ocelot
                | Ocelot
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Bastard took my hand... How could he have gotten in here?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-liquid
                | Liquid
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Perhaps there's a spy among us... Mantis is dead.  We've also got to find out what killed Baker and Octopus.  We're shorthanded, so make this little torture show of yours as short as possible.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-ocelot
                | Ocelot
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Torture?  This is an interrogation.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-liquid
                | Liquid
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | As you wish. (Liquid turns to Snake.)
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-liquid
                | Liquid
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | See you later, brother... (Liquid leaves.  Wolf walks up to Snake.)
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-wolf
                | Wolf
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Your woman is still in this world...
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Meryl...
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-wolf
                | Wolf
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Catch you later, handsome... (Wolf leaves.)
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-ocelot
                | Ocelot
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Once she picks a target, she doesn't think about anything else. Sometimes she even falls in live with thwm before she kills them. Finally, just the two of us.  How are you feeling?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Not bad.  I caught a nice nap on this revolving bed of yours.  Too bad I was sleeping alone.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-ocelot
                | Ocelot
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Glad to hear that.  This is some bed all right.  I'm about to show you some of its nicer features...
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Where are my things?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-ocelot
                | Ocelot
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Oh don't worry.  They're all there.  Washington was taking quite a chance sending you here.  Someone must have had a lot of faith in your skill.  Huh, carrier boy?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | So, Metal Gear is armed with a new type of nuclear warhead, huh?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-ocelot
                | Ocelot
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Why don't you go ask Campbell for the full story?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | The Colonel?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-ocelot
                | Ocelot
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | By the way, you get an optical disk from President Baker, didn't you?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | What if I did?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-ocelot
                | Ocelot
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Is that the only disc?  There's no other data?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | What do you mean?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-ocelot
                | Ocelot
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | There's no copy?  If not, that's fine.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Is Meryl okay?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-ocelot
                | Ocelot
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | She's not dead yet.  Wolf must have been feeling generous.  But if you want her to stray that way you better start answering my questions right now.  You were holding one card key.  Where are the other two?  What's the trick behind that key!?  That weasel of a president said there's some kind of trick to using the key.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Hell if I know.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-ocelot
                | Ocelot
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | I see.  No problem then.  We're going to play a game, Snake.  And we'll find out what kind of man we really are.  When the pain becomes too great to bear just give up and your suffering will end.  But if you do, the girl's life is mine. (Snake is brought back to his cell.  He sees a dead body laying in the corner.)
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Looks like I've got a roommate.  The DARPA Chief!?  Whew...what a stench! (Campbell calls on the Codec.)
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-campbell
                | Campbell
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Snake, are you okay?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | I've been better.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-naomi
                | Naomi
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | How's Meryl?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | ........
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-campbell
                | Campbell
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | ........ Snake, the government has decided not to give in to their demands.  We're trying to buy some more time.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | C'mon, Colonel.  Why don't you stop playing dumb?  I'm sorry about Meryl but I want the lies to end now.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-campbell
                | Campbell
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | What are you talking about?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Metal Gear was designed to launch a new type of nuclear warhead, wasn't it?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-campbell
                | Campbell
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | !
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | You knew it all along, didn't you?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-campbell
                | Campbell
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | .......
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Why did you try to hide it?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-campbell
                | Campbell
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | ...I'm sorry...
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Can't tell the grunts, huh?  ...You've changed a lot.  Metal Gear... secret advanced nuclear weapons research...  Does the White House know about this?  How deep does it go?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-campbell
                | Campbell
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | As far as I know, as of yesterday, the President had not  been briefed about the Rex Project.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | "Need to know basis", is that the idea?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-campbell
                | Campbell
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | These are sensitive times.  Even sub-critical nuclear tests are causing quite a stir.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Plausible deniability, huh?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-campbell
                | Campbell
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Yes.  And tomorrow the President and his Russian counterpart are scheduled to sign the Start 3 Accord.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | I get it.  That's the reason for the deadline.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-naomi
                | Naomi
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | That's right, Snake.  And that's why we can't let the terrorist attack go public.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-campbell
                | Campbell
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | We still haven't even ratified Start 2 or dealt with the issue of TMDs.  This has to do with the Presodent's reputation and America's place as the dominant superpower.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | So patriotism is your excuse for circumventing the Constitution?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-campbell
                | Campbell
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Please, Snake... just stop them.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Why should I?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-campbell
                | Campbell
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Because you're the only one who can.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | In that case, tell me the truth about this new type of nuclear warhead.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-campbell
                | Campbell
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | I told you before.  I don't knwo the details.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | I don't believe you.If the situation is so serious, why don't you give in to their demands?  Let them have Big Boss's remains.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-campbell
                | Campbell
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | You see...
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Or is there some reason that you can't do that?  Something you haven't told me about?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-naomi
                | Naomi
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Publicly, the President has been very vocal in his opposition to eugenics experiments.  We don't want the existance of the Genome Army to go public.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | And that's the only reason?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-campbell
                | Campbell
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | .......
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Huh!  The hell with you!
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-campbell
                | Campbell
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | I'm sorry.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | The corpse of the DARPA Chief is lying right here next to me.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-naomi
                | Naomi
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Poor man.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | But it's strange.  He looks and smells like he's been dead for days. All his blood's been drained out too.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-campbell
                | Campbell
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Drained!?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-naomi
                | Naomi
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Maybe to slow down decomposition?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | I have no idea.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-naomi
                | Naomi
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | But the Chief only died a few hours ago, right?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Right.  But he's already started to decompose.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-naomi
                | Naomi
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | What could it all be about?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | SOmething in his blood that they wanted?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-naomi
                | Naomi
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | I doubt it.  Just the nanomachines and the transmitter.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-campbell
                | Campbell
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Did the Chief tell them his detonation code?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | I'm afraid so.  It looks like they've got both codes and are nearly ready to launch.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-campbell
                | Campbell
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Damn.  Is there any way to prevent it?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | It seems there's some type of emergency override device that can cancel out the detonation code.  It's a countermeasure that ArmsTech installed secretly.  You have to unlock it with three special card keys.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-campbell
                | Campbell
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | And where are those keys?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | I've got one of them.  I don't know where the other two are. Besides, I'm locked up here.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-campbell
                | Campbell
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | We've got no choice.  Forget about the keys.  Your top priority now is to destroy Metal Gear itself.  Sorry to lay it all in your lap, but you're all I've got.  Bust out of there and get to the Communications Tower.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-naomi
                | Naomi
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | .......
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | .......  Naomi, please talk to me.  Say something to take my mind off the pain.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-naomi
                | Naomi
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | What can I say?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Anything.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-naomi
                | Naomi
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | I...I'm not a very good talker.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Please... tell me about yourself.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-naomi
                | Naomi
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Myself?  That's a tough one...
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Any family?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-naomi
                | Naomi
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | That's not a very happy topic for me.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | I don't have any family.  No wait, there was a man who said he was my father...
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-naomi
                | Naomi
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Where is he?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Dead.  By my own hand.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-campbell
                | Campbell
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Big Boss.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-naomi
                | Naomi
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | What!? Big Boss!?  I had no idea.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-campbell
                | Campbell
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | There was no way you could.  It happened in Zanzibar 6 years ago. Only Snake and I know the real truth of what happened there.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-naomi
                | Naomi
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | So, is it true?  Was Big Boss really your father?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | That's what he said.  That's all I know.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-naomi
                | Naomi
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | And you were able to kill him, knowing that?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Yup.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-naomi
                | Naomi
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | How?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | He wanted it.  Besides, some people just need killing...
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-naomi
                | Naomi
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | That's patricide.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Yup.  That's the trauma that Mantis was talking about.  The one we share in common.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-naomi
                | Naomi
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Is that why you left FOX-HOUND?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Let's just say that I needed to be alone for a while and Alaska was the perfect place...
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-naomi
                | Naomi
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | ...Snake... I didn't have a real family either.  Just a big brother who put me through school.  We weren't even blood-related and he was much older than me.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Where is he?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-naomi
                | Naomi
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | He's dead...
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | I'm sorry.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-naomi
                | Naomi
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | ...Snake, is there a woman in your life?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | After you've been through as many wars as me, it's hard to trust anyone.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-naomi
                | Naomi
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Friends?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Roy Campbell...
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-campbell
                | Campbell
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Huh?  You're still calling me friend?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-naomi
                | Naomi
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Is that it?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | No, there was another... Frank Jaeger.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-naomi
                | Naomi
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | What!?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-campbell
                | Campbell
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Big Boss's most trusted lietenant and the only member of FOX-HOUND to ever recieve the codename "Fox".  Gray Fox.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-naomi
                | Naomi
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | ........
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | I learned a lot from him.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-naomi
                | Naomi
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | But... didn't you try to kill each other?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | That's true.  We did.  In Zanzibar.  But it was nothing personal. We were just proffesionals on opposite sides, that's all.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-naomi
                | Naomi
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | And you still call yourselves friends?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Hard to believe?  War is no reason to end a friendship.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-naomi
                | Naomi
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | That's insane.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | I first met him on the battlefield.  He was being held a prisoner of Outer Heaven.  But he didn't look like a prisoner to me.  He was always so cool and precise.  I was still green and he showed me the ropes.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-naomi
                | Naomi
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | You knew him well?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | No.  We never talked about our personal lives.  Sort of an unwritten rule.  The nest time I saw him on the battlefield, we were enemies.  We were fighting barehanded in a minefield.  I know it sounds strange to most people.  But we were just two soldiers doing our jobs.  It's like a sport.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-naomi
                | Naomi
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Men and their games!  You're like wild animals!
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | You're right.  We are animals.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-naomi
                | Naomi
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | So if you were friends, then how do you explain the Ninja's behavior?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | I don't know.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-naomi
                | Naomi
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | It's your genes... they make you predisposed towards violence!
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | You really like talking about genes, Naomi.  Why did you get into genetic research anyway?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-naomi
                | Naomi
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | I never knew who my parents were or even what they looked like. I guess I got into genetics because I wanted to figure out why I'm the way I am.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | So you studied about DNA?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-naomi
                | Naomi
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Yeah.  I thought if I studied my genetic structure, I'd find out who I really was.  I thought that by analyzing a person's genetic information, I could retrieve the blank spots in that person's memory.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Memory is stored in DNA?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-naomi
                | Naomi
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | We're not sure.  But we know that a person's genetic fate is determined just by the sequence of the four bases in their DNA.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | So what about my fate? You know my DNA sequence, don't you?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-naomi
                | Naomi
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Your fate?  I...I'm sorry.  I have no idea.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Of course not.  You're a scientist, not a fortune-teller.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-naomi
                | Naomi
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | ......... (Snake ends his talk with Naomi and calls Otacon.)
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Otacon, are you still okay?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-otacon
                | Otacon
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Yeah.  Thanks to the stealth camouflage, that is.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | I have a favor to ask.  I need your help.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-otacon
                | Otacon
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | I was wondering when you'd ask.  What should I do?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | I've been captured.  I'm locked up here in this cell.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-otacon
                | Otacon
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | What cell?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | There's a big torture machine nearby.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-otacon
                | Otacon
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Okay.  I know it.  It's close.  I'll be there right away.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Thanks. (Snake waits for Otacon to arrive.  The guard who si watching Snake has a bowel attack.)
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-guard
                | Guard
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Aaachoo!  That witch!  She took my clothes!  Oh... my stomach. (The guard goes to the bathroom.)
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-otacon
                | Otacon
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Hey! I'm here! (Snake looks around but doesn't see anybody.)
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Where?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-otacon
                | Otacon
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Here. (Otacon takes off his stealth camouflage.  He is by the cell door.)
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-otacon
                | Otacon
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | It's me.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Otacon!
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-otacon
                | Otacon
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Wow!  They even captured you! (Snake grabs Otacon and shakes him.)
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Hurry!  Get me out of here!
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-otacon
                | Otacon
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Let me go!  That hurts!
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Hurry up!
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-otacon
                | Otacon
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Is that how you ask a guy a favor?  Let me go.  Jeez, it's like an animal's cage.  ...What a smell! (Snake points to the DARPA Chief.)
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Because of him.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-otacon
                | Otacon
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Eeyaaah!  It's the DARPA Chief!!
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | If you don't hurry up and get me out of here, I'll be laying next to him.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-otacon
                | Otacon
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Those bastards!  This lock won't open up with a security card.  You need a key like the soldiers carry.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | So what are you doing here then? (Otacon reaches into his coat and pulls two objects out.)
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-otacon
                | Otacon
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | I... I thought you might be hungry.  If you need more food, I can bring some more later. (He has ketchup and a hamburger.)
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-otacon
                | Otacon
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Also, I got this level 6 card, it'll get you out of that torture room. Here... take this too. (Otacon takes yet another thing out of his coat.)
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | What's that.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-otacon
                | Otacon
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | It's a hankerchief.  I got it from Sniper Wolf.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Why?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-otacon
                | Otacon
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | I don't know why, but she's nice to me.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Sounds like Stockholm Syndrome to me.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-otacon
                | Otacon
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | I was taking care of the dogs here.  After the terrorists take over, they were planning to shoot all the dogs.  But Sniper Wolf stopped them... she even let me feed them when I asked.  She likes dogs.  She must be a good person.  Please don't hurt her.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Wake up you idiot!  She's the one who shot Meryl!
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-otacon
                | Otacon
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Well, that's all I can do...
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | They're planning to launch a nuke!  I've got to stop them!
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-otacon
                | Otacon
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Then you'll have to get past the Communications Tower.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | First, you have to get me out of here!
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-otacon
                | Otacon
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | C'mon...I'm trying my best...
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | That guard's got the key.  You'll have to take him out!
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-otacon
                | Otacon
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Gimme a break!  I'm no soldier!  I can't take anybody out!
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | You have to!!
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-otacon
                | Otacon
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | I'll be killed! (The guard opens the bathroom door.)
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-otacon
                | Otacon
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Oh jeez.  He's coming back... see ya later... (Otacon turns and leaves.)
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Wait! (Snake waits for the guard to come back.  He breaks the ketchup bottle and uses it to make fake blood.  The guard is alerted.)
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-guard
                | Guard
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | What the hell! (The guard rushes into the cell and Snake quickly takes him out.  After getting all his stuff Snake heads for the Communications Tower.  Snake gets to the spot where Meryl was shot.  He stops and thinks back.) (Meryl is shot in both legs.  She collapses to the ground.  Meryl tries to reach her gun beside her.  The sniper acts quickly and shoots her in the arm.)
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-meryl
                | Meryl
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Aaaaaaaaahhhh!!! (She collapses in a pool of blood and tries to reach her gun beside her.  The sniper acts quickly and shoots her in the arm.)
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-meryl
                | Meryl
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Aaaaaaaghhhh!!! (Meryl gives up and lies on her back, bleeding badly.  Snake tries to move towards her, but he is met by a bullet that hist the wall right near him.)
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-meryl
                | Meryl
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Snake.... leave me and run...
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Meryl...
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-meryl
                | Meryl
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | I guess... I am a rookie after all...
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Don't worry, Meryl.  It's me they want.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-meryl
                | Meryl
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Even I know that, it's the oldest trick in the book.  The sniper's using me for bait to lure you out.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Damn!!
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-meryl
                | Meryl
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Shoot me, Snake!!
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | No!
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-meryl
                | Meryl
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | My gun... I can't reach it by myself.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Don't move!
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-meryl
                | Meryl
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | I promised... I wouldn't slow you down!  I... I... I can still help... I want to help you!
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Quiet down!  Save your strength!
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-meryl
                | Meryl
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | I was a fool, I wanted to be a soldier.  But war is ugly... There's nothing glamorous about it.  Snake, please!  Save yourself.  Go on living and don't give up on people!  Don't forget me... (Campbell calls on the Codec.)
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-campbell
                | Campbell
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Snake, about Meryl...
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Colonel, I'm sorry...
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-campbell
                | Campbell
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Listen to me.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | I wasn't able to protect her.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-campbell
                | Campbell
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Snake, it's okay.  You did what you could, now let it rest.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Colonel...
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-campbell
                | Campbell
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | She joined up of her own free will.  I'm sure she was prepared for this.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | No.  You're wrong.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-campbell
                | Campbell
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | ...?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Meryl thought she had to become a soldier... thought it was the only way.  She said she thought it woul;d bring her closer to her dead father.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-campbell
                | Campbell
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | She said that!?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | She wasn't ready for real combat.  I shouldn't have pushed her so hard.... It's all my fault.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-master
                | Master
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | That's not like you, Snake.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-campbell
                | Campbell
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Master.  What is it?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-master
                | Master
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Sorry for eavesdropping, but I just couldn't listen anymore.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Master...
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-master
                | Master
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Snake, you can have regrets if you want to... it's only natural. But you can't keep attacking yourself for things that happened in the past.  That road leads to madness, believe me.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-mei-ling
                | Mei Ling
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | He's right.  Don't kick yourself.  It doesn't suit a legend like you. And besides that, for all we know Meryl's okay, right?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Mei Ling...
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-campbell
                | Campbell
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Snake, forget about Meryl.  Stop Liquid.  That's what Meryl would want, too.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | You're right.  Meryl would say the same thing.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-naomi
                | Naomi
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Snake.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | What?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-naomi
                | Naomi
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Meryl...she's pretty special to you, huh?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Yes, she's special.  There aren't many women like her around.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-naomi
                | Naomi
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | That's not what I meant...
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | She's the Colonel's niece... and a combat buddy.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-naomi
                | Naomi
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Is that all?  C'mon...
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | This is like a police interrogation.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-naomi
                | Naomi
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | No, I just...
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-campbell
                | Campbell
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | I guess it's in the genes...
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | The genes?  What are you talking about, Colonel?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-campbell
                | Campbell
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | No, I just remembered about Naomi's grandfather.  I think Naomi said he rose as high as assisstant secretary in the FBI during Edgar Hoover's time.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog.dialog-snake
            em.name.name-snake
                | Snake
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Is that right?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-naomi
                | Naomi
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Yes...yes, he was Japanese and he became a special undercover investigator to nab the mafia.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-master
                | Master
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | When was that?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-naomi
                | Naomi
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Oh.. sometime in the 50's, I guess.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-master
                | Master
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Where?
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-naomi
                | Naomi
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | New York, I think...
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-master
                | Master
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Naomi, I thought you didn't have any family...
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-naomi
                | Naomi
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Well...I...I researched it after I became an adult.  My grandfather was already dead by the time I learned about him.  I never even had the chance to meet him.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-campbell
                | Campbell
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Oh...
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-naomi
                | Naomi
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Snake, good luck.
            p.msg.msg-cn
                | NULL
        .dialog
            em.name.name-campbell
                | Campbell
                span :
            p.msg.msg-en
                | Watch your back, Snake.
                | (Snake signs off and heads for the Communications Tower.  he reaches the top but as soon as he tries to cross to the second tower it is destroyed by missile fire.)
